  }
  system_message {
    message: "[Message] timestamp=2026-07-21T06:11:53Z sender=5dd056da-3000-42a9-9068-a9bed0aa8658/task-31 priority=MESSAGE_PRIORITY_HIGH content=Task id \"5dd056da-3000-42a9-9068-a9bed0aa8658/task-31\" finished with result:\nCommand output:\nDownloading Pinterest image...Image downloaded successfully!Analyzing image with Gemini...--- DESIGN ANALYSIS FROM GEMINI ---This is a breakdown of the high-end, futuristic dark-mode landing page design (**\"Recognito\"**). While originally presented as a Web3 infrastructure landing page, this aesthetic translates into an incredibly premium, high-converting **developer portfolio** or SaaS showcase.It features a \"Sliced Wave\" or vertical-slat parallax background, glowing amber/orange accents, floating interactive HUD elements, and ultra-clean glassmorphism typography.---### 1. Color PaletteThe design utilizes a high-contrast dark theme punctuated by intense, radiant orange and amber glows that give a volcanic, energy-infused aesthetic.| Color Role | Hex Code | Tailwind CSS Equivalent | Usage || :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- || **Deep Background** | `#080808` | `bg-neutral-950` / `bg-[#080808]` | Main viewport canvas background || **Slat Borders** | `#ffffff08` | `border-white/5` | Faint divider lines for vertical layout columns || **Accent Glow (Base)**| `#3a1400` | `bg-orange-950/40` | Low-frequency background ambient lighting || **Accent Glow (Mid)** | `#ff5c00` | `bg-orange-600` | Vibrant mid-tone wave lights || **Accent Glow (High)**| `#ffb076` | `bg-amber-300` | Core highlight/hotspot within the wave || **Text Primary** | `#ffffff` | `text-white` | Header, core title accents, primary CTAs || **Text Secondary** | `#a1a1aa` | `text-zinc-400` | Subtitles, secondary pill badges, body text |---### 2. TypographyThe design relies on a premium, geometric sans-serif font family. Excellent choices include **Plus Jakarta Sans**, **Inter**, or **SF Pro Display**.*   **Main Hero Title:** High-contrast weight pairing.    *   *\"Meet! Recognito\"* uses a **Medium/Semibold** weight (`font-semibold tracking-tight text-white`).    *   *\"Built for a secure Web3 future.\"* uses a **Light/Thin** weight (`font-light text-zinc-100`).*   **Navigation Links:** Micro-typography (`text-xs tracking-wider font-medium text-zinc-400`).*   **HUD Nodes / Badge Labels:** Small-scale monospace or tight tracking sans-serif (`text-[11px] tracking-wide uppercase font-medium`).---### 3. Layout & Grid Architecture (The \"Vertical Slats\" Grid)The core structure of the landing page is not a traditional grid block, but a **Vertical Strip Layout** overlaying a fluid background canvas.```+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+|  [Logo]                       [  Home  Private Key  Product ...  ]           [Join Beta] |  <- Header+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+|   |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |     ||   |         |         |         | [Badge] |         |         |         |         |     |  <- Foreground Content|   |         |         |       Hero Text Block       |         |         |         |     |     (Absolute Centered)|   |         |         |        [CTA Buttons]        |         |         |         |     ||   | [Node]  |         |         |         |         |         | [Node]  |         |     |  <- Floating interactive |   |         |         | [Node]  |         |         |         |         |         |     |     HUD elements|   |         |         |         |  [Orb]  |         | [Node]  |         |         |     ||   |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |     || c1|   c2    |   c3    |   c4    |   c5    |   c6    |   c7    |   c8    |   c9    | c10 |  <- 10x Vertical Slats+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+```*   **Slat Containers:** The screen is divided into 10 equal columns (`grid-cols-10`). Each column has a faint right border (`border-r border-white/[0.04]`).*   **The Sliced Wave:** The glowing orange background runs *behind* these columns. By offsetting the vertical position of the glow asset inside each column slightly, you create the \"glitched wave\" or \"stepped equalizer\" effect.---### 4. Component Deep Dive#### A. Header & Navigation Bar*   **Logo:** White text paired with a dual-circle overlapping logo (a glowing amber circle merging with a dark grey circle).*   **Navigation Capsule:** A glassmorphic capsule anchored in the center of the header:    *   `backdrop-blur-md bg-zinc-950/40 border border-white/5 rounded-full px-5 py-1.5`*   **Primary CTA Button (\"Join Beta\"):**    *   High-contrast pill container: `bg-white text-black hover:bg-zinc-200 transition-all font-medium px-5 py-1.5 rounded-full text-xs`.#### B. Floating HUD Nodes (Interactive Metrics/Tags)Scattered dynamically over the column grid, these pins denote structural hubs or key stack attributes (e.g., \"Secured\", \"Light Speed\", \"Encrypted\", \"Center HUB\"):*   **Design:** A small horizontal pill container with a semi-transparent dark grey background (`bg-zinc-950/60 border border-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm`).*   **Visual Indicator:** Connected to a precise focal point or light source using a tiny glowing connector line and a dot (`h-1.5 w-1.5 bg-orange-500 rounded-full animate-ping`).#### C. Floating Orbital Core (Hero Centerpiece)Positioned near the lower-center of the screen.*   **Structure:** A heavy dark circle (`bg-neutral-950`) with an intense inner drop-shadow (`box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.8)`).*   **Insignia:** An intersecting duo-ring glyph glowing with an orange-to-yellow gradient.*   **Glow Ring:** Backed by an external radial shadow blur (`shadow-[0_0_50px_rgba(249,115,22,0.35)]`) that pulses slowly.---### 5. Tailoring for a Developer PortfolioTo transform this layout into an elite developer portfolio:*   **Vertical Slats:** Use the vertical columns to represent different projects or phases of your stack (e.g., Column 1-3: Frontend, Column 4-6: Backend, Column 7-10: DevOps).*   **Floating HUD Nodes:** Replace \"Encrypted\" or \"Center HUB\" with your active tech stack or key metrics (e.g., `\"99.9% Uptime\"`, `\"React/Next.js\"`, `\"Rust/Wasm\"`).*   **The Orbital Core:** This central orb can display your personal avatar or initials, radiating glow outward.---### 6. Micro-interactions & Framer Motion ImplementationTo bring this UI to life, implement these responsive animations:#### Dynamic Mouse Parallax on Vertical SlatsAn interactive movement where the vertical slats shift slightly relative to the mouse cursor\'s coordinates.```javascript// Framer Motion variant for an individual vertical slatconst slatVariants = {  hover: (customIndex) => ({    y: [0, customIndex % 2 === 0 ? -12 : 12, 0],    transition: {      duration: 8,      repeat: Infinity,      ease: \"easeInOut\"    }  })};```#### Ambient \"Glow Wave\" PulseThe amber light needs to feel alive. Use a custom CSS animation keyframe in your Tailwind configuration:```css@keyframes wavePulse {  0%, 100% {    opacity: 0.6;    filter: saturate(100%) blur(60px);  }  50% {    opacity: 0.95;    filter: saturate(140%) blur(80px);  }}.animate-wave-pulse {  animation: wavePulse 6s ease-in-out infinite;}```#### Magnetic CTAsApply a magnetic pull effect to the primary button (`Apply for Beta`) and the navigation capsule. This can be built using Framer Motion tracking `clientX` and `clientY` with spring-based damping coordinates:```javascriptimport { motion, useMotionValue, useTransform } from \"framer-motion\";export function MagneticButton({ children }) {  const x = useMotionValue(0);  const y = useMotionValue(0);  const handleMouseMove = (e) => {    const { clientX, clientY, currentTarget } = e;    const { left, top, width, height } = currentTarget.getBoundingClientRect();    const centerX = left + width / 2;    const centerY = top + height / 2;    x.set((clientX - centerX) * 0.35); // Pull strength multiplier    y.set((clientY - centerY) * 0.35);  };  const handleMouseLeave = () => {    x.set(0);    y.set(0);  };  return (    <motion.button      onMouseMove={handleMouseMove}      onMouseLeave={handleMouseLeave}      style={{ x, y }}      transition={{ type: \"spring\", stiffness: 150, damping: 15 }}    >      {children}    </motion.button>  );}```------------------------------------"
    render_info {
      title: "Running script to get portfolio design specification from image finished"
