    thinking: "**Analyzing Design Elements**\n\nI\'m incredibly impressed with \"Recognito,\" this futuristic, high-end portfolio style. The deep dark slate (#080808) foundation paired with glowing amber/orange accents creates a striking contrast that feels both modern and sophisticated. The name itself reflects a thoughtful design choice.\n\n\n**Visualizing Core Components**\n\nI\'m now picturing the \"Vertical Slats\" grid, overlain by a glowing background. Each column will have faint right borders, and offset orange glows within each column to form that \"glitched wave\" effect. I\'m focusing on the glassmorphic navigation capsule and logo, and the floating HUD nodes \342\200\223 small, dynamic glass boxes scattered over the grid and linked to glowing dots. The Hero Centerpiece? A pulsing neon orb! The motion library, as it is now installed is `motion: ^12.23.24`.\n\n\n**Refining Responsive Framework**\n\nI\'m now integrating crucial features. Dark mode, plus full responsiveness with Tailwind CSS, will be key. I\'m prioritizing multiple interactive sections: a Hero Section with vertical slats, floating HUD nodes, and an orbiting core; an Experience Timeline spanning Dhanush\'s 20-year career; and an interactive Bento Showcase. I\'m excited about the custom glowing effects!\n\n\n"
