  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Drafting Component Files**\n\nI\'m now focusing on drafting the modular component files, starting with `/src/components/SlatBackground.tsx`. This background component will use `grid-cols-10` for its 10 vertical columns, incorporate subtle divider lines, implement mouse-tracking parallax glows, and incorporate floating animations. This will form the visual foundation of the design.\n\n\n**Conceptualizing Background Visuals**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the \"stepped equalizer\" effect for the background. The core idea is clear: an absolute glowing shape behind a grid of 10 columns, each with an offset glow that matches its index. Animating these column glows at different speeds creates the \"glitched visualizer\" effect, which is perfect for the design brief. I\'m imagining it as an offset orange glow circle in each column, creating the stepped wave profile. I plan to use Framer Motion for the animations to give it that alive look.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 145814805
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
