tive space balance. Key metrics are now incorporated, including 100% Component Token Compliance, a +45% Higher Client Satisfaction, and Perfect Responsive Adaptation. I am confident I\'ve added excellent data points.\n\n\n**Analyzing Card Layout**\n\nI\'m now analyzing the card layout structure, and I\'m very excited about the data points for the Digital Marketing, Mobile, Web and Design categories. I\'m focusing on emulating the `itboomi.com` sticky card arrangement. I\'m considering using a vertical stack with a container div, and each card set as `sticky` to the top. I\'ve got to ensure the `z-index` increments for stacking. I am confident I\'m close to a working structure.\n\n\n**Implementing Card Scaling**\n\nI\'m now implementing card scaling for a more dynamic visual experience. I\'ve decided to refine the scaling logic. The aim is for older cards to shrink as they\'re scrolled past. I\'ve also found an approach that allows easy Framer Motion transitions, or even pure CSS. I am excited to see how this translates. I am now thinking about index-based scaling to create an elegant overlay effect.\nI\'m also considering the design for each card, including a premium horizontal desktop layout and a stacked mobile layout, with interactive hover states on the images.\n\n\n**Designing Landing Animation**\n\nI\'m now designing the landing animation. I\'m taking inspiration from `marat_ga`\'s work, especially the bold typography and kinetic effects. The goal is a cinematic experience with a dark screen that reveals \"MEET DHANUSH\" in a split-text, letter-by-letter transition. I\'m focusing on a loading animation with a percentage, glassmorphic glow elements, and dynamic elements. Large shadows that stack over each other, creating real physical depth will give it a stunning feel.\n\n\n**Animating Typography**\n\nI\'m now diving into the typography animation. Each letter in \"Meet Dhanush\" will be masked within a div, sliding up with a slight rotation and spring effect. I\'ve been researching premium designer animations, and I\'ve decided on a detailed implementation: a preloader counts to 100 with a glow, then fades to reveal a staggered transition of the landing elements and the animated \"Meet Dhanush\" title.\n\n\n**Implementing Mouse Interactions**\n\nI\'m now implementing interactive mouse effects. As the mouse hovers, letters scale, change color, and glow. A horizontal typographic marquee will scroll in the background to create a parallax feel. I\'m taking inspiration from Pinterest, for a mesmerizing \"first screen\" design. I\'m going to start with a new state.\n\nI\'m starting a new preloader! I\'m going to add a new `isLoaded` state, and I\'m going to build a high-fidelity counter preloader. It will occupy the full screen, and the counter will increase from 0 to 100 in about 1.8 seconds.\n\n\n"
