  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Gathering Font Details**\n\nI\'ve successfully pinpointed the exact font specifics! I now have the stylesheet details, including `--font-sans` as \"Plus Jakarta Sans,\" `--font-display` as \"Space Grotesk,\" `--font-serif` as \"Playfair Display\" (a beautiful italicized font!), and `--font-mono` as \"JetBrains Mono\". This gives me a much stronger starting point!\n\n\n**Designing Hero Animation**\n\nI\'m now focused on crafting a stunning typography reveal within the hero section, breaking down the name \"Dhanush\" into animated characters. My plan involves a letter-by-letter, perhaps word-by-word, reveal for a striking visual effect. The current strategy is to split the name string and render each character with an animation.\n\n\n**Refining Animation Strategy**\n\nI\'ve been iterating on the animation strategy, now focused on optimizing the hero section\'s typography reveal. I\'m leveraging React\'s `motion.span` component to animate individual characters, with subtle variations in delay and easing to create a dynamic visual rhythm. The \"Dhanush\" name is now using a serif font with an italic style, creating a more refined look. Further, I\'ve incorporated a hover effect for enhanced user interaction, aiming for a smooth and engaging experience.\n\n\n**Refining the Animation**\n\nI\'ve hit a breakthrough! This character-by-character reveal, with the letters masked by an `overflow-hidden` container and sliding up with rotation and scaling is exactly the high-end animation I wanted. It\'s incredibly professional-looking and responsive, like the best Awwwards sites. Now, I\'m integrating this animation with a monospace preloader on mount, featuring a progress bar from 0 to 100 to reveal the rest of the section beautifully.\n\n\n**Implementing Preloader Logic**\n\nI\'ve just implemented the preloader with a smooth, dynamic progress bar from 0-100%, updating at 60 FPS. I\'m using an interval to increment a `loadingProgress` state, which drives the visual progress. Once 100% is reached, a short delay ensures the user sees completion before the preloader fades. I\'m also now using various loading phrases for each stage of loading: \"ESTABLISHING SECURE PROTOCOLS...\", \"MOUNTING CORE KINETIC MATRICES...\", etc. The display uses a black background with a giant styled number and phrases.\n\n\n**Adding Landing Animation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the final reveal, the \"core ready\" moment. The preloader\'s progress bar smoothly completes at 100%, and I\'m using `AnimatePresence` to orchestrate its graceful exit. The preloader will fade out and scale up, or slide up, to unveil the landing elements. To give it a premium feel, I\'m exploring a horizontal scrolling marquee, a signature high-impact typography element, using Framer Motion\'s `useScroll` and `useTransform` to make a stylish scrolling background text.\n\n\n**Implementing Marquee Effect**\n\nI\'ve just implemented a horizontal marquee background! I\'m using `useScroll` and `useTransform` from Framer Motion to create the effect. It\'s working seamlessly by horizontally offsetting two `motion.div` elements. One marquee scrolls to the left, and another, with a reverse transform, scrolls to the right!\n\n\n**Refining Scroll Effects**\n\nI\'m now refining the scroll effects of the marquee design and the parallax, as well as the initial load-in elements! The opposite scrolling banners are looking fantastic, and I\'m ensuring they smoothly transition and maintain performance during user scroll interactions, with Framer Motion, using its `useScroll` and `useTransform` hooks to control the animation. The scrolling is giving me a great impression. The overall look is stunning.\n\n\n"
