  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the New Layout**\n\nI\'m now diving into the `ProjectShowcase.tsx` file, examining how projects are currently defined. I\'ve noted the stacking card implementation on `itboomi.com` as a visual reference for this design. I\'m moving away from a grid layout, seeking a more unique stacking approach.\n\n\n**Refining the Stack Implementation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the dynamic offset and scaling for the card stacking effect. Thinking about sticky positioning and how to cascade the cards, I\'m leaning toward a solution where each card has a slightly different top offset to reveal the one beneath it. I am trying to determine the correct CSS rules that should apply to the cascading offsets. The goal is a visually appealing and layered stacking.\n\n\n**Implementing the Dynamic Layout**\n\nI\'ve been tinkering with the cascading sticky top offsets and z-index to get the stacking effect right. The goal is now working, with each card revealing a sliver of the one beneath it. I\'m focusing on refining the offset calculation for an ideal visual balance and adjusting the `top` values and their spacing. The current plan utilizes `top: `${110 + index * 20}px` and I am now experimenting with the exact values to ensure an aesthetically pleasing stack.\n\n\n**Adjusting Card Styling**\n\nI\'m now focusing on card styling with conditional classes and transformations. I\'ve implemented a subtle scale-down for older cards to provide visual depth. Also, I\'ve added a decorative glowing backdrop for each card. I\'m dynamically choosing colors for these backdrops based on the card index.\n\n\n**Analyzing Card Content**\n\nI\'m now diving into the content details within each card. I\'m focusing on the index counter and category display, and thinking through different ways to dynamically render them. The goal is to ensure a clean and readable layout. I\'m taking the index + 1 and presenting it as `0{index + 1}` to keep a consistent visual presentation. Then, the category display is being considered, where it\'s being represented as an uppercase, rounded pill. I am looking at its font family, weight, size, and coloring.\n\n\n**Refining the Card Structure**\n\nI\'m now implementing the content components within each card, focusing on the subtitle and description elements. I\'m leveraging conditional styling to maintain visual consistency in both light and dark modes. I\'m focusing on text size and spacing to ensure readability and balance within the card layout. I\'m exploring the use of `line-clamp-3` for multi-line text truncation to keep the card concise.\n\n\n**Implementing Tag Rendering**\n\nI\'m now integrating the project tags into each card, making sure they integrate cleanly with the overall design. I\'m dynamically generating these tags, paying close attention to their visual presentation. I am currently considering the application of conditional styles for light and dark modes, ensuring readability and consistency across all themes. The plan is to create a visual grouping, with a small dot and a text label to the right. The plan is to keep these tags as small, rounded pills.\n\n\n\n**Integrating Media and Tags**\n\nI\'m now integrating the right-side media panel and tag rendering within the card. I\'ve successfully incorporated the image with hover zoom, along with a transparent gradient overlay to ensure text legibility. I\'m focusing on positioning the hover inspect overlay correctly. The new plan ensures the tags render properly within the card, maintaining the original visual design of the components.\n\n\n**Reviewing Component Imports**\n\nI\'m now taking a close look at the component imports to ensure everything is streamlined and nothing is missed. I\'m confirming all necessary elements are present and properly linked, especially the `ExternalLink` component used for the \"Inspect Stack\" button. I am making sure everything matches and implements the current styles, colors, and behaviors. I\'m also confirming the proper importing of `motion` and `AnimatePresence`.\n\n\n"
